Key Match Events: Tanner Bibee gave up five earned runs on eight hits, including three solo home runs, but also struck out six batters with 11 swings and misses.
Bo Naylor hit a solo home run in the seventh inning, sparking a comeback for the Cleveland Guardians.
Steven Kwan and Andres Gimenez followed up with base hits, both scoring via a Josh Naylor single and a Will Brennan single.
Will Brennan scored the go-ahead run on a Jhonkensy Noel base hit to right field.
Andres Gimenez made a spectacular catch in the top of the eighth inning, preventing Freddy Fermin from reaching base and potentially changing the game's outcome.
